/* Negative test: error location reset after a function body.

   Regression for the `currentStatementSrc` staleness bug. After parsing a function body,
   `currentStatementSrc` retained the last in-body statement's location. A subsequent
   global-scope error then reported the WRONG file:line — pointing at a line inside
   the function body rather than at the offending global-scope construct.

   The trailing const declaration is missing both type and `=` (`const NAME 31;`),
   triggering the "Missing type before identifier" error. The fix ensures the error
   reports the actual const's line (20), not the last in-body statement (line 18). */
// EXPECT_ERROR: _test_source_location_after_function.bgl:21
// EXPECT_ERROR: Missing type before identifier
#beguilerSettings { target = z5; informName = "none"; outputPath = "tests/output"; }

void someFunction(){
    int x = 1;
    int y = 2;
    int z = x + y;
}

const SOMENAME 31;
